(189, 'Lansoprazole 15mg 5 caps - لانسوبرازول', '  Lansoprazole', 'الوصف لانسوبرازول هو مثبط مضخة البروتون الذي يمنع المعدة من إنتاج الحمض. يتم تصنيعها عن طريق الصنبور المنتجات الصيدلانية الآلية من lansoprazole ينتمي إلى فئة من مركبات مضاد الإفراز ، والبديل بديزيميدازولز ، التي لا تظهر خصائص مضادات مستقبلات مضادات الكولين أو الهيستامين H2 ، ولكن بدلا قمع إفراز حمض المعدة عن طريق تثبيط محدد من (ح + ، ك + ) -تنظام نظام إنزيم على السطح الإفرازي للخلية الجدارية المعدة. نظرًا لأن نظام الإنزيم هذا يعتبر كمضخة حمضية (بروتون) داخل الخلية الجدارية ، فقد تم وصف لانسوبرازول كمثبط لمضخة الحمض المعدي ، حيث أنه يمنع الخطوة النهائية لإنتاج الحمض. هذا التأثير مرتبط بالجرعة ويؤدي إلى تثبيط إفراز الحمض المعدي القاعدي والمحفز بغض النظر عن الحافز.', NULL, 1, 14.40, '2020-08-30 10:31:35', '2020-08-30 10:31:35'),
(190, 'Macrofuran 100 mg 30caps -', '  Nitrofurantoin', 'About nitrofurantoinnitrofuran derivative antibiotic, urinary germicide, miscellaneous antibiotic.mechanism of action of nitrofurantoinnitrofurantoin is a bacteriostatic drug. it undergoes enzymatic reduction and produces active metabolite which damages the dna of the bacteria. bacteria reduce nitrofurantoin more rapidly than mammalian cells.indications for nitrofurantoin1. urinary tract infectioninteractions for nitrofurantoinantichlolinergic drugs: bioavailability of nitrofurantoin increased due to delayed gastric emptying. probenecid: decreased renal clearance and increased serum levels of nitrofurantoin resulting in toxicity. magnesium trisilicate: may delay or decrease the absorption of nitrofurantoin. food: increases bioavailability of nitrofurantoin. lab tests: serum glucose decreased. elevated serum bilirubin and alkaline phosphates. elevated urinary creatinine levels. false-positive urinary glucose using benedicts reagent.', NULL, 1, 21.00, '2020-08-30 10:31:35', '2020-08-30 10:31:35'),
(191, 'Nizatect 150 mg 20 hard gelatin caps -', '  Nizatidine', 'Indication for the treatment of acid-reflux disorders (gerd), peptic ulcer disease, active benign gastric ulcer, and active duodenal ulcer.pharmacodynamics nizatidine is a competitive, reversible inhibitor of histamine at the histamine h2-receptors, particularly those in the gastric parietal cells. by inhibiting the action of histamine on stomach cells, nizatidine reduces stomach acid production. nizatidine had no demonstrable antiandrogenic action. full-dose therapy for the problems treated by nizatidine lasts no longer than 8 weeks. it has been demonstrated that treatment with a reduced dose of nizatidine is effective as maintenance therapy following healing of active duodenal ulcers.mechanism of action nizatidine competes with histamine for binding at the h2-receptors on the gastric basolateral membrane of parietal cells. competitive inhibition results in reduction of basal and nocturnal gastric acid secretions.', NULL, 1, 30.00, '2020-08-30 10:31:36', '2020-08-30 10:31:36'),
(192, 'Nitromak retard 5mg 30 caps -', '  Nitroglycerin', 'Indication for the prevention of anginapharmacodynamics nitroglycerin, an organic nitrate, is available in many forms as a vasodilator. nitroglycerin is used in the treatement of angina pectoris and perioperative hypertension, to produce controlled hypotension during surgical procedures, to treat hypertensive emergencies, and to treat congestive heart failure associated with myocardial infarction.mechanism of action similar to other nitrites and organic nitrates, nitroglycerin is converted to nitric oxide (no), an active intermediate compound which activates the enzyme guanylate cyclase. this stimulates the synthesis of cyclic guanosine 3 ,5 -monophosphate (cgmp) which then activates a series of protein kinase-dependent phosphorylations in the smooth muscle cells, eventually resulting in the dephosphorylation of the myosin light chain of the smooth muscle fiber. the subsequent release of calcium ions results in the relaxation of the smooth muscle cells and vasodilation.', NULL, 1, 22.50, '2020-08-30 10:31:36', '2020-08-30 10:31:36'),
