(1050, 'Profusol 600mg 20 s.g. caps -', '  Ibuprofen', 'About ibuprofennsaid, a propionic acid derivative, analgesic and anti-inflammatory.mechanism of action of ibuprofenibuprofen has analgesic, anti-inflammatory and antipyretic action. it acts by inhibiting prostaglandin (pgs) synthesis and their release at the site of injury. prostaglandins cause tenderness and amplify the action of other algesics. ibuprofen inhibits cyclo-oxygenase enzyme and antagonizes prostaglandin actions. it also inhibits platelet aggregation and prolongs bleeding time.indications for ibuprofen1.rheumatoid arthritis 2.ankylosing spondylitis 3.acute gout 4.joint disorders e.g. inflammatory disease in joints, crystal deposition in the joints 5.osteoarthritis 6.for the relief of fever, pain and inflammation in dental, minor surgery and orthopedic 7.dysmenorrhoea 8.juvenile arthritis 9.migraine 10.patent ductus arteriosus(iv)', NULL, 1, 9.50, '2020-08-30 10:39:16', '2020-08-30 10:39:16'),
