(1113, 'Oravit b12 1 mg s.r. 10 caps -', '  Vitamin b12', 'Indication for treatment of pernicious anemia (due to lack of or inhibition of intrinsic factor) and for prevention and treatment of vitamin b 12 deficiency.mechanism of action vitamin b12 is used in the body in two forms: methylcobalamin and 5-deoxyadenosyl cobalamin. the enzyme methionine synthase needs methylcobalamin as a cofactor. this enzyme is involved in the conversion of the amino acid homocysteine into methionine. methionine in turn is required for dna methylation. 5-deoxyadenosyl cobalamin is a cofactor needed by the enzyme that converts l-methylmalonyl-coa to succinyl-coa. this conversion is an important step in the extraction of energy from proteins and fats. furthermore, succinyl coa is necessary for the production of hemoglobin, the substances that carries oxygen in red blood cells.', NULL, 1, 18.00, '2020-08-30 10:39:45', '2020-08-30 10:39:45'),
