(1270, 'Rofcox 12.5mg/5ml 120ml susp -', '  Rofecoxib', 'About rofecoxibnsaid,selective cox-2 inhibitor, analgesic ,anti-inflammatory.mechanism of action of rofecoxibrofecoxib inhibits prostaglandin synthesis by inhibiting cox2 enzyme. this nsaid inhibit cox2 enzyme selectively (cox-2 is only produced in response to tissue injury and causes tissue inflammation, and thus pain. it works converting arachidonic acid into a specific prostaglandin which communicates the need for inflammation to the surrounding tissue). this results the anti-inflammatory actionindications for rofecoxib1. dysmenorrhea (pain with your menstrual period) 2. osteoarthritis', NULL, 1, 22.50, '2020-08-30 10:41:04', '2020-08-30 10:41:04'),
(1271, 'Coprimasept oral susp. 100 ml -', '  Sulphamethoxazole+trimethoprim', 'Indication for the treatment bacterial infections causing bronchitis, prostatitis and urinary tract infections.mechanism of action sulfonamides inhibit the enzymatic conversion of pteridine and p-aminobenzoic acid (paba) to dihydropteroic acid by competing with paba for binding to dihydrofolate synthetase, an intermediate of tetrahydrofolic acid (thf) synthesis. thf is required for the synthesis of purines and dtmp and inhibition of its synthesis inhibits bacterial growth. pyrimethamine and trimethoprim inhibit dihydrofolate reductase, another step in thf synthesis, and therefore act synergistically with the sulfonamides.', NULL, 1, 5.25, '2020-08-30 10:41:05', '2020-08-30 10:41:05'),
