(1490, 'Paramol 120mg/5ml syrup 125ml -', '  Paracetamol(acetaminophen)', 'About paracetamolacetanilide derivative, non narcotic analgesic,antipyretic.mechanism of action of paracetamolparacetamol has analgesic and antipyretic action. it is more active on cyclo-oxygenase enzyme in brain. peripherally it is a poor inhibitor of prostaglandin synthesis. analgesic action: paracetamol raises the pain threshold and produces analgesic effect. antipyretic action: paracetamol lowers fever by direct action on the thermoregulatory centre in the hypothalamus and block the effects of endogenous pyrogen. indications for paracetamol1. to relieve pain and fever 2. acute gout 3. migraine interactions for paracetamolcholestyramine: reduces absorption of paracetamol. charcoal: activated, administered immediately reduces absorption of paracetamol. domperidone and metochlopramide: enhance absorption of paracetamol. alcohol: chronic excessive ingestion of alcohol potentiates hepatotoxicity of paracetamol.', NULL, 1, 12.00, '2020-08-30 10:42:51', '2020-08-30 10:42:51'),
(1491, 'Avil 0.3gm/100ml syrup 100ml (cancelled) -', '  Pheniramine', 'About pheniramine maleatefirst generation histamineh1 antagonist ,alkylamine derivative, anti histamine.mechanism of action of pheniramine maleatethis alkyl amine derivative has peripheral h1 receptor antagonist action and compete with histamine for binding to the receptors present on bronchi, uterus etc. this inhibits the activation of receptors and corresponding allergic symptoms produced by it. centrally the drug also has some antimuscarinic activity.indications for pheniramine maleate1. eczema 2. dermatitis 3. urticaria 4. skin oedema 5. itching due to insect bites 6. photo-dermatitis 7. rhinitis 8. serum sickness 9. paresis during pregnancy 10. toxaemia and retention of placenta 11. motion sickness', NULL, 1, 5.75, '2020-08-30 10:42:52', '2020-08-30 10:42:52'),
