(2171, 'Statergic 2.5mg/5ml ophthalmic sol. 5 ml -', '  Epinastine', 'Description epinastine is used for the prevention of itching associated with allergic conjunctivitis. it has a multi-action effect that inhibits the allergic response in 3 ways: 1. stabilizes mast cells by preventing mast cell degranulation to control the allergic response, 2. prevents histamine binding to both the h1- and h2-receptors to stop itching and provide lasting protection, and 3. prevents the release of proinflammatory chemical mediators from the blood vessel to halt progression of the allergic response.mechanism of action epinastine has a multiaction effect that inhibits the allergic response in 3 ways: 1. stabilizes mast cells by preventing mast cell degranulation to control the allergic response, 2. prevents histamine binding to both the h1- and h2-receptors to stop itching and provide lasting protection, and 3. prevents the release of proinflammatory chemical mediators from the blood vessel to halt progression of the allergic response.', NULL, 1, 10.00, '2020-08-30 10:52:33', '2020-08-30 10:52:33'),
