(2319, 'Oxycinon 5 i.u./ml amp -', '  Oxytocin', 'Mechanism of action of oxytocinoxytocin binds to g-protein coupled receptors. in human myometrium these receptors couple to gq and g11 receptors. this will activate phospholipase -c hydrolysis and generate inositol triphosphate (ip3) and diacyl glycerol. these will mobilizes calcium ion from calcium deposits and also enhances voltage sensitive ca2+ channels. this ca2+ produces contraction. oxytocin also increases local prostaglandin production and stimulates uterine contractions.indications for oxytocin1. induction of labour 2. augmentation of labour 3. reduction of postpartum bleeding 4. induce abortion 5. oxytocin challenge test interactions for oxytocinsympathomimetics: pressor effect of sympathomimetics may be increased leading to postpartum hypertension. prostaglandins: risk of uterine repture & cervical lacerations. ergotamine: synergistic effect in control of post partum haemorrhage.', NULL, 1, 1.50, '2020-08-30 10:53:46', '2020-08-30 10:53:46'),
(2320, 'Pirocam sterile i.m. 3 amp -', '  Nicotinamide+piroxicam', 'About nicotinamidewater soluble vitamin(b complex- vitamin b3), amide of nicotinic acid.mechanism of action of nicotinamidenicotinamide exerts its action by influencing metabolic reactions. it is converted in to coenzymes ncotinamide adenine dinucleotide (nad) and its phosphate ncotinamide adenine dinucleotide phosphate (nadp) involved in oxidation reduction reactions. these pyridine nucleotides act as hydrogen acceptors in the electron transport chain in tissue respiration, glycolysis, and fat synthesis. nicotinic acid in high doses has vasodilator effects and also improves lipid profile- reduces serum cholesterol, raises hdl level, lowers vldl, and ldl levels.indications for nicotinamide1.pellagra 2.niacin deficiency 3.hartnup disease typical dosage for nicotinamidepellagra: 200 to 500mg daily in divided doses. prophylactically: 20 to 50mg daily. dietary supplement: 10 to 20mg daily hartnup disease: 50 to 200mg daily in divided doses.', NULL, 1, 6.00, '2020-08-30 10:53:47', '2020-08-30 10:53:47'),
(2321, 'Bendatreotid 0.2mg/ml soln. for subcutaneous inj -', '  Octreotide', 'About octreotideanalogue of somatostatin, a cyclic octapeptide, hormonal agent, acromegaly.mechanism of action of octreotideoctreotide is a potent synthetic octapeptide analogue of somatostatin. the drug exerts it`s action by inhibiting the secretion of growth hormone (gh), thyroid stimulating hormone (tsh), prolactin in pituitary- insulin and glucagons in pancreas, and all gastrointestinal secretions including gastrin and hcl. it constricts splanchnic, hepatic, and renal blood vessels. it decreases blood flow to gastrointestinal mucosa and also has antisecretory actions on the gut. it controls diarrhea due to suppression of hormones which enhance intestinal mucosal secretion.indications for octreotide1.carcinoid tumors 2.vasoactive intestinal peptide secreting tumors (vipomas) 3. acromegaly 4.severe acute bleeding from intestinal varices, gastric or duodenal ulcers, or haemorrhagic gastritis.', NULL, 1, 400.00, '2020-08-30 10:53:47', '2020-08-30 10:53:47'),
