(2602, 'Streptomycin sulphate 1gm i.m.vial -', '  Streptomycin', 'About streptomycinaminoglycoside antibiotic, antitubercular agent.mechanism of action of streptomycinstreptomycin exerts it`s bactericidal action against gram- negative organisms & some of gram positive organisms by inhibiting bacterial protein synthesis. the process involves 1. penetration of bacterial cell membrane & binding directly to the 30 s subunit of bacterial ribosome, 2. misleading of m-rna codon by bacterial ribosome, 3. formation of peptide chains with wrong amino acid sequence which gets incorporated into bacterial cell membrane and alters it`s permeability, 4. bacterial cell lysis.indications for streptomycin1.tuberculosis 2.brucellosis 3.tularemia 4.plague 5.enterococcal endocarditis interactions for streptomycinaminoglycosides, amphotericin b, bacitracin, cisplatin, cephalothin, vancomycin, methoxyflurane ethacrynic acid, frusemide, bumetanide & mannitol: increased ototoxic, neurotoxic or nephrotoxic affects.', NULL, 1, 5.00, '2020-08-30 10:56:13', '2020-08-30 10:56:13'),
(2603, 'Streptolase 1.5 miu i.v vial -', '  Streptokinase', 'About streptokinasea plasminogen activator, antithrombotic.mechanism of action of streptokinaseit exerts it`s fibrinolytic action by activating natural fibrinolytic system. it causes lysis of thrombus or clot and thus recanalyses occluded blood vessels such as coronary artery. it combines with plasminogen to form an activator complex which causes proteolysis of plasminogen molecules to plasmin (fibrinolysin). plasmin converts insoluble fibrin to soluble fibrin fragments.indications for streptokinase1.acute myocardial infarction 2.pulmonary embolism 3.venous thrombosis 4.arterial thromboembolic disorders 5.thrombophlebitis', NULL, 1, 350.00, '2020-08-30 10:56:13', '2020-08-30 10:56:13'),
(2604, 'Unictam 750 mg vial i.m/i.v -', '  Ampicillin+sulbactam', 'About sultamicillinpenicillinsmechanism of action of sultamicillinsultamicillin is an oral form of the antibiotic combination ampicillin/sulbactam. it contains esterified ampicillin and sulbactam. sulbactam is an irreversible inhibitor of most important beta - lactamases, that occur in penicillin- resistant organisms. ampicillin is the bactericidal component of the combination, as it inhibits the biosynthesis of cell wall mucopeptide of many gm +ve, gm- ve aerobic and anaerobic bacteria. indications for sultamicillin1.upper respiratory tract infections including sinusitis, otitis media and tonsillitis. 2.lower respiratory tract infections including bacterial pneumonias and bronchitis. 3.urinary tract infections and pyelonephritis. 4.skin and soft tissue infections and gonococcal infections.', NULL, 1, 16.00, '2020-08-30 10:56:14', '2020-08-30 10:56:14'),
