(2794, 'Terbinafine 1% topical aerosol powder -', '  Terbinafine', 'About terbinafinea synthetic allylamine derivative, antifungal.mechanism of action of terbinafineterbinafine is a fungicidal drug. it interfere the conversion of squalene to ergosterol by inhibiting the enzyme squalene epoxidase.this results in accumulation of squalene in the fungal cells and leads to membrane distortion and death of the fungus.indications for terbinafine1. tinea pedis 2. tinea corporis 3. tinea capitis 4. tinea cruris 5. onychomycosis interactions for terbinafinecimetidine: terbinafine clearance is decreased 33%. rifampicin: terbinafine clearance is increased 100%. terfenadine: terbinafine clearance is decreased 16%. cyclosprorin: clearance of cyclospronine increased by 15%.', NULL, 1, 48.75, '2020-08-30 10:57:47', '2020-08-30 10:57:47'),
(2795, 'Resinokaten 454g powder -', '  Sodium polystyrene sulphonate', '*potassium binders are medications that bind potassium ions in the gastrointestinal tract, thereby preventing its intestinal absorption. they consist of polystyrene sulfonate resins attached to a cation and are administered either orally or by retention enema to patients who are at risk of developing hyperkalaemia (abnormal high serum potassium levels). increased serum potassium levels are a condition likely to occur in patients suffering from chronic kidney disease in advanced stages.*daily adult dose is 15 gm to 60 gm (15 gm =4 level teaspoons) one to four times daily.contraindicated in obstructive bowel disease.', NULL, 1, 260.00, '2020-08-30 10:57:47', '2020-08-30 10:57:47'),
(2796, 'Deflax 12 sachets -', '  Simethicone+sorbitol', 'About simethiconeoral anti-foaming agent, silicones, antiflatulent.mechanism of action of simethiconethis anti-gas (anti-flatulence) medication acts in the stomach and intestines to change the surface tension of gas bubbles, enabling smaller bubbles to join together into bigger bubbles. it results elimination of gas more easily by belching or passing flatus.indications for simethicone1. abdominal pain which is due to excessive gas in the digestive tract 2. before gastroscopy or radiography of the bowel typical dosage for simethiconeoral- adults and teenagers- 60 -125mg four times a day, after meals and at bedtime. not more than 500 mg should be taken in twenty-four hours. chewable tablets: adults and teenagers- 40 -125 mg four times a day, after meals and at bedtime or 150 mg three times a day, after meals. not more than 500 mg should be taken in twenty-four hours. suspension: adults and teenagers- 40 -95 mg four times a day, after meals and at bedtime.', NULL, 1, 2.50, '2020-08-30 10:57:48', '2020-08-30 10:57:48'),
(2797, 'Sorbit 5 gm 20 sachets -', '  Sorbitol', 'About sorbitola sugar alcohol, sweetener, non-stimulant laxative, osmotic diuretic, genitourinary irrigant.mechanism of action of sorbitolsorbitol is hydrolysed in the colon to short chain fatty acids. this fatty acid stimulates colonic propulsive motility by osmotically drawing water into the lumen.', NULL, 1, 6.80, '2020-08-30 10:57:48', '2020-08-30 10:57:48'),
